== English ==
=== Etymology ===
Colander derives from the [[Middle English]] ''colyndore'' and [[Old Provençal]] ''colador'' (meaning a strainer).

=== Pronunciation ===
*{{audio|en-uk-word.ogg|Audio (UK)}}

=== Noun ===
'''colander'''
# A bowl-shaped [[kitchen]] [[utensil]] with holes in it used for [[drain]]ing food such as [[pasta]].

